      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Why would anyone buy stocks if bonds are safer?</summary>
        <p>Because stocks historically offer significantly higher long-term returns. While bonds are safe, their returns are often very low and may struggle to keep up with inflation. Stocks are required to generate meaningful wealth over long periods.</p>
      </details>
